---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Engage"
  description="Engage the authors of Revenue Architecture. The FACT Intake — an agentic scoping conversation — is launching soon. For now, reach us directly."
>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-content px-6 py-20 md:py-28">
    <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-teal">Engage</p>
    <h1 class="mt-4 max-w-prose text-4xl leading-tight md:text-5xl">
      Tell us what you are trying to fix.
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-6 max-w-prose text-lg text-ink">
      Soon you will be able to talk to the FACT Intake — an agentic scoping conversation
      that runs the RAOS FACT qualification: Fit, Authority, Criteria, Timeline. It is
      launching in phase 2. Until then, the form below reaches us directly.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-navy-100/40">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-content px-6 py-section">
      <div class="grid gap-10 md:grid-cols-5">
        <!-- FACT teaser -->
        <div class="md:col-span-2">
          <div class="rounded-card border border-dashed border-teal-300 bg-teal-100/40 p-6">
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-teal-600">
              Coming soon — phase 2
            </p>
            <h2 class="mt-2 text-xl text-teal-900">The FACT Intake</h2>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink">
              An agentic conversation that qualifies the engagement against four tests:
            </p>
            <ul class="mt-3 space-y-1 text-sm text-ink">
              <li><span class="font-semibold text-navy">Fit</span> — are you the kind of firm we serve?</li>
              <li><span class="font-semibold text-navy">Authority</span> — are the right decision-makers engaged?</li>
              <li><span class="font-semibold text-navy">Criteria</span> — what do you need, and how will you judge success?</li>
              <li><span class="font-semibold text-navy">Timeline</span> — is there a compelling reason to act now?</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!--
          PLACEHOLDER FORM — Laura: this form is intentionally non-functional.
          There is no backend wired up. When the FACT Intake (phase 2) ships, this
          should either post to the intake agent or to a real handler/CRM.
          For now it does nothing on submit (preventDefault) and just shows a note.
        -->
        <div class="md:col-span-3">
          <form
            class="rounded-card border border-navy-100 bg-surface p-6"
            onsubmit="event.preventDefault(); document.getElementById('form-note').hidden = false;"
            aria-describedby="form-note"
          >
            <h2 class="text-xl">Reach the authors</h2>
            <div class="mt-5 space-y-4">
              <div>
                <label for="name" class="block text-sm font-semibold text-navy">Name</label>
                <input id="name" name="name" type="text" autocomplete="name" class="mt-1 w-full rounded-card border border-navy-100 px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:border-orange focus:outline-none focus:ring-1 focus:ring-orange" />
              </div>
              <div>
                <label for="email" class="block text-sm font-semibold text-navy">Email</label>
                <input id="email" name="email" type="email" autocomplete="email" class="mt-1 w-full rounded-card border border-navy-100 px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:border-orange focus:outline-none focus:ring-1 focus:ring-orange" />
              </div>
              <div>
                <label for="company" class="block text-sm font-semibold text-navy">Company</label>
                <input id="company" name="company" type="text" autocomplete="organization" class="mt-1 w-full rounded-card border border-navy-100 px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:border-orange focus:outline-none focus:ring-1 focus:ring-orange" />
              </div>
              <div>
                <label for="problem" class="block text-sm font-semibold text-navy">What are you trying to fix?</label>
                <textarea id="problem" name="problem" rows="4" class="mt-1 w-full rounded-card border border-navy-100 px-3 py-2 text-sm focus:border-orange focus:outline-none focus:ring-1 focus:ring-orange"></textarea>
              </div>
            </div>
            <button
              type="submit"
              class="mt-6 inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-card bg-orange px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-surface transition-colors hover:bg-orange-600"
            >
              Send
            </button>
            <p id="form-note" hidden class="mt-4 text-sm text-teal-700">
              This is a placeholder form — no message was sent. A real handler ships with phase 2.
            </p>
          </form>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Talk to a human -->
      <p class="mt-10 max-w-prose text-sm text-ink">
        Prefer a person? You can always reach a human. Email
        <a href="mailto:contact@revenuearchitects.com" class="font-semibold text-orange transition-colors hover:text-orange-600">contact@revenuearchitects.com</a>
        and one of the authors will reply. No bot wall, no qualification gate to get a first conversation.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
